+8. Links to deeper docs by topic.
 
-That stack also maps cleanly to how I think about technical writing work for engineering-led companies. Teams do not need decorative documentation. They need pages that reduce time-to-first-useful-change. That is the standard I use for product docs, internal docs, and the kind of developer content I write for clients on [my work page](/work).
